Australian Open 2012: Novak Djokovic throws shirt to girl in crowd, sees it snatched by different woman
Competition was fierce in Melbourne on Sunday, with participants slugging it out for a gruelling six hours in order to take home the coveted prize on offer. By Telegraph staff
11:55AM GMT 30 Jan 2012
Comments
We're talking, of course, about the battle for position for the main event at the Australian Open final, and the epic contest for Novak Djokovic's sweat-stained shirt.
Following the Serb's epic win over Rafael Nadal he headed for the crowd and appeared to be aiming for a specific fan when he chucked his t-shirt.
Instead an entirely different lady swept in to steal the glory and a tasteful white number, which she then held up to inspect as if it was a blouse in H&M that she isn't quite sure about.
It's the acceptable face of opportunism.
